title: Walk with Me
description: A community of monks in France led by Zen Buddhist master Thich Nhat Hanh offers an intimate glimpse into mindfulness practice and the monastic life.

title: Warrior Women
description: Lucy Lawless hosts this five-episode documentary series about history's fiercest female fighters, from Joan of Arc to Apache combat tactician Lozen.

title: Water & Power: A California Heist
description: California residents and farmers face powerful barons in the struggle to secure water rights in this fresh historical account of profit and interests.

title: Waterschool
description: Six young women, who each live near one of Earth's major rivers, share how the Waterschool environmental education program has impacted their lives.

title: We Are Twisted F***ing Sister!
description: Before achieving mainstream success in the 1980s, glam rock icons Twisted Sister spent years crafting their outrageous act in the New York club scene.
actors: Dee Snider, Mark Mendoza, Jay Jay French, Eddie Ojeda

title: We Speak Dance
description: Trained dancer Vandana Hart travels the world to learn traditional and urban dance styles from the local experts who know them best.

title: What Happened, Miss Simone?
description: Using never-before-heard recordings, rare archival footage and her best-known songs, this is the story of legendary singer and activist Nina Simone.

title: What the Health
description: This film examines the link between diet and disease, and the billions of dollars at stake in the healthcare, pharmaceutical and food industries.

title: What We Started
description: DJs and industry insiders offer a backstage pass to the world of electronic dance music, reflecting on its radical origins and the future of the genre.

title: White Right: Meeting the Enemy
description: To many, white supremacists embody hate in its purest form. One filmmaker decides to look past the rhetoric to see if a human connection is possible.

title: Why Knot
description: Pressured by his traditional family to marry, a filmmaker explores the idea of monogamy and the possibility of lifelong union without sexual fidelity.

title: Why We Fight: The Battle of Russia
description: This installment of Frank Capra's acclaimed documentary series highlights the need for a Russo-American alliance to defeat the Nazis.

title: Without Gorky
description: A filmmaker trains the camera on her own family as she examines the impact her grandfather, troubled artist Arshile Gorky, had on three generations.

title: Wizard Mode
description: Pinball wizard Robert Gagno trains his focus on becoming a world pinball champion while simultaneously challenging social assumptions about autism.

title: World of Compulsive Hoarders
description: Four compulsive hoarders are driven to accumulate objects but can't bear to throw them out -- to the point where their "stuff" takes over their lives.

title: World’s Heaviest Man Gets Married
description: After losing 400 of his 1225 pounds, Mexico's Manuel Uribe faces logistical obstacles as he prepares to marry his longtime girlfriend.

title: WWII: Report from the Aleutians
description: Filmmaker John Huston narrates this Oscar-nominated World War II-era film about life among the U.S. soldiers protecting Alaska’s Aleutian Islands.
